@NODE installation
@{B}@{U}Information@{UU} : @{UB} Flexy can be modified in easy way, so to
avoid maximum fake versions, I choose to sign it with PGP 2.6.3i. I invite
you to check it, before updating it.

My PGP pub key is available on request.

How to check: PGP:PGP ram:flexy.sig ram:flexy

@{B}@{U}Installation@{UU} : @{UB}
Best is to use the installation script provided in package. It should
process all correctly, well... I hope. ;-)

If you prefer to install it manualy, respect the following:

- Copy Flexy directory where you want. But if you want to use the catalog
of your language, you need to copy it to Locale:Your_language/ or make
Flexy directory as autopath like assign or Path add.
Eg: "Path DH2:my_dir/flexy/ add ".

- A good way is to use SYS:Tools/Flexy path.

- Check stack is set to 12000 or more.

You NEED also to use some other software: ARexx must be launch, AwnPipe must
be mount (L:awnpipe.handler and Mount awnpipe: (inside a Shell or CLI)).
Library RexxReqTools.library must be in Libs:

See the documentation of each program...

@ENDNODE

@NODE Presentation "Presentation"
@{U}Note@{UU}: ARexx must be launched and AwnPipe: mount. See
@{"installation" LINK installation} page.

Easy to use, Flexy uses the three following clicktabs:

1) ClickTab @{"options" LINK onglet1} gives a way to activate/desactivate all
   V2.4+ FlexCat options.

2) ClickTab @{"Commands" LINK onglet2} is the main window of Flexy. Use it to set-up
   and start the catalogs compilation.

3) ClickTab @{"Settings" LINK onglet3} will give you a way to use some Flexy settings and
   to Load/save options.

4) Some Key stroke @{"Shortcut" LINK gen}.

You can now quit Flexy by a normal way with the close gadget or use either
the menu item, or the Quit button in third clicktab gadget or use ESC key.

@ENDNODE

