@NODE Onglet2  "ClickTab Commands"
@{B}Commands :@{UB}

Select the name of description catalog file. (Source)
Select the name of initial or new translation file.
Select the name of second translation file if update needed.
Select the name of final catalog file. (Destination)

Both gadgets (buttons) to the right of description and translation fields
provide a way to make an automatic copy of the file name and its path to the
field below and to add the right extension.

First gadget will react only in creation translation mode and in others
modes if translation file exists.

@{B}Mode@{UB} :

   @{U}Make catalog@{UU} : Create a catalog file from a description file and a
   translation file.

   @{U}Update translation@{UU} : Make an update of a translation file from a
   (new) description file and an (old) translation file.

   @{U}Make translation@{UU} : Make the first translation file from
   a description file.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Onglet3  "ClickTab Settings"
@{B}Settings :@{UB}

- Clever mode (names): a 'clever' management of filenames from description
  file which provide an automatic choice (if exists) of other files with
  automatic extensions. Eg: `File.cd' => `File.ct' and `File.catalog'.

- Add path in fields: Add in other fields the path used above.

@{fg highlight}*@{fg text} - Default path : You can enter here the working
  directory used a lot for your translations work.
  When this field is empty, it's the 'PROGDIR:' (where Flexy was launched)
  path which is used.

  This option can be used mixed with 'Clever mode names' but it can becaomes
  ennoying when using differents path for each type of files like '.cd',
  '.ct' or '.catalog'. I, this case, disable 'Clever mode'.

  This option became obsolete the one on 'Add path in fields', anyway,
  feature is prety different and can be useful for some people, so I kept
  it. I had hardly break my mind on conception to not remove a work... ;-))

                        ---------------------------

- Load settings at launch: Load Flexy settings when it launch. Else it use
  a default configuration.

- Ask before to quit: Show a request to confirm the quit action.
  Flexy do not says if settings were modified or not!

- Create log file for Flaxcat messages: when this option is activated,
  errors and warning messages than Flexcat could send, are saved in
  'RAM:Flex_Error' file.

Note than messages like that when making un update :
Prgs:Sources/language.ct, ligne 215. Warning: ID MSG_Msg_win, is missing
 from .ct.
is not realy an error, that's just to inform you the string isn't in the
initial .ct file. Logicaly, it could appear in the new .ct file (updated)
with comment ;***NEW*** just below.

                        ---------------------------

- Both buttons « Load » and « Save » are used to load and save the Flexy
  settings. Flexcat options and Flexy prefs are put in a Flexy.config
  located to `S:'.

Note: « Load » button is available only if a config file already exists.
      (saved a previous one).

@ENDNODE

@NODE utilisation "Utilisation"
@{fg highlight}*@{fg text}
Well, here how to use Flexy with efficiency.

The default settings are good enough for most of work then usage is done
by clicktab Commands:

@{b}A/ How to make a '.ct' file?@{ub}

1) Select 'Make translation' in Mode cycle gadget.

2) In first field 'Description' place your 'Flexy.cd' file by using the
file gadget between the name of field and field itself.

3) By default, the correct name 'Flexy.ct' is filled automaticly in the
second field 'Translation' with the full path of previous field.
Example: 1) Description: DH4:Translations/Flexy.cd
         2) Translation: DH4:Translations/Flexy.ct

Your are free to chose any location.

4) Click on 'Compile' button.

5) The screen make flash (Bip), if option 'Create log file...' is set in
'Settings' clicktab, you can find in a file named 'RAM:Flex_error' with
the errors or warnings reporting by Flexcat.


@{b}B/ How to update a '.ct' file?@{ub}

You already have a '.ct' file and got a new '.cd' file then to update the
translation file without loose your previous job, play like that: ;)

1) Select 'Update translation' in Mode cycle gadget. The third field will be
available.

2) and 3) like @{b}A@{ub} section

3 bis) if the translation named is not using exactly the description
basename, you have to select the file with the file-requester (gadget).
Example: 'Flexy.cd' and 'Flexy_Fr.ct' the part '_Fr' will not be handle
automaticly.

The third field 'Updated .ct' should display the name of the updated '.ct'
file with an extra 'N' at end like 'Flexy.ctN'. N stand for 'New'. ;-)

4) and 5) as previous.

Now you just have to go in your favorite editor and update the translation
file. I suggest you rename old '.ct' file '.ct_old' and '.ctN' by '.ct'.


@{b}C/ How to create a catalog '.catalog' file?@{ub}

1) Select 'Make catalog' in Mode cycle gadget. The third field will be
disalable.

2) and 3) like @{b}A@{ub} section

3 bis) if the translation named is not using exactly the description
basename, you have to select the file with the file-requester (gadget).
Example: 'Flexy.cd' and 'Flexy_Fr.ct' the part '_Fr' will not be handle
automaticly.

4) and 5) as previous.

Check catalog errors using Catcheck (Aminet) of Sönke Tesch to verify
the conformity between '.cd', '.ct' and '.catalog' files.

That's all... :)

More tips:

@{b}D/ I've work a lot and each dir-path are far away from default path@{ub}

To get back on default path, you have two choices:
  1) Load settings, (menu or 'settings' clicktab).
  2) Click on GetDir defalt path gadget and validate by ok.

In both cases, default path will be back in the four string fields.

@ENDNODE

@NODE gen "Shorcuts"

`ESC' key is used to quit the window (Flexy) (with confirmation or not in
function of your settings set in @{"Settings" LINK onglet3} clicktab).
`ESC' will also quit the other information windows.

The `Return' key is used to validate a field or to say `Ok' in other windows.

